screen_name: Our family got COVID-19. It was very scary for a bit, but we all had mild cases. I’m less surprised that we tested positive than that we were tested at all. I wrote about it here: https://t.co/Bb7sR4bXv6
Malaised and Confused: Linklater’s film in the works about COVID19
Hubs has a headache, I have a sore throat, and I can't tell if this sort of journalism is important or irresponsible: https://t.co/rP8oRmSXWw

Over the next few months, many of us will either get COVID-19 or be paranoid about getting it, worrying that every minor ache/ sore throat/ cough is a symptom. Maybe that's one reason the boomers are so blasé. If they worried about every ache and cough they'd do nothing else.
Very anxious about supplies of hydroxychloroquine for people who need it to treat their autoimmune diseases. Like me. Pharmacies out of stock. Thanks Trump!
